Role Purpose
Under the Supervision of Global Information Security and Business continuity Director, Global Information Security and Business Continuity Manager will manage Information Security and business continuity activities, ensure that FINCA Impact finance is compliant with Information Security and Continuity Policies and Best Practices, maintain and Implement Management Practices for Standardization and Effective Management of Information security and Continuity in FIF network, centrally oversee and coordinates IS and BCM activities in FIF Network, Validate the Status and Support in Definition of Improvement Action Plans for Raising Maturity. The incumbent will act as a Main Point of contact and Subject Matter Expert for Subsidiaries IS and BCM Professionals in FIF Network, maintain Holistic visibility on the Information Security and Business Continuity level within FIF Network, coordinate and Support When Necessary IS and BCM initiatives Within the FIF Network.
The Success of this role is measured by achievements gained during the appropriate reporting period, annual performance review and increased overall maturity in Information security and Business continuity.

Accountabilities
Investigate, recommend, evaluate, deploy and integrate security tools and techniques to improve our ability to protect corporate assets and infrastructure;
Assess and capture security requirements within context of enterprise application architecture;
Ensure that application development and deployment meet FINCA security standards;
Provides security input to design and application architectural reviews;
Monitor security logs and incidents;
Document security and compliance of applications and supporting infrastructure;
