Act as the Key party in Projects from Information Security and Business Continuity side;
Ensure integration of Information Security and Business Continuity with FIF Business Strategy and objectives;
Guide and assist Subsidiary IS and BCM staff for Effective Management of Information Security and Business Continuity Program;
Support Subsidiaries with Information Security and Business Continuity Issues coordination, action plan definition and follow up;
Educate and train Subsidiary IS and BCM staff;
Conduct Subsidiary IS and BCM Status Assessment, Identify Gaps and Deliverables;
Perform Information and Data Security Risk Assessment per Requirement;
Perform Business Continuity Assessments;
Define Goals and Deliverables for Improving IS and BCM Maturity;
Periodic Follow up with Subsidiaries on IS and BCM activities;
Conduct Business Impact Analysis (BIA);
Recovery Strategies and Produce Corresponding Documentation (BCP, BRP, DRP) ;
Produce Periodic Reporting for Subsidiary IS and BCM Status;
Coordinate Crisis Activities;
Coordinate Exercises such as Disaster Recovery, Business Recovery, Crisis Management.
Job Requirements
Qualifications
Bachelor's degree in a technical discipline or equivalent work experience in Information Technologies and/or Information Security;
Certifications are not required but will be considered in the evaluation process. Applicable certifications include:
Information Security: SANS, Splunk, CISSP, CISM, or ISO 27001, Cobit, NIST or Relevant
Business Continuity: CBCI, MBCI, CBCP, MBCP or Relevant
Experience
Minimum 5 years' experience in Information Security Management and additional experience in Information Technology Management
Minimum 3 years' experience in Management
Strong experience with Enterprise Level Security Technologies (SIEM, DLP, Endpoint Protection, Vulnerability Assessment, etc.)
Proven record of Successful Management of Information Security and Business Continuity activities
Minimum 3 years' Experience in Microfinance and/or Banking on similar role

Knowledge and Skills
Excellent Knowledge of Information Security Principles, Concepts, Controls and Processes
Excellent Knowledge of Business continuity and Crisis Management Principles, Concepts, Controls and Processes
In-depth knowledge of Information Technologies, Systems, Networking Principles
Good Understanding of Banking and Microfinance Business, Business objectives
Excellent Computer Skills
Proactive Response Skills
Team Player
Ability to work in stressful environment
Able to manage simultaneously multiple activities involving various stakeholders and to deliver results within deadlines.
Excellent communication (oral and written) and interpersonal skills.
Proven ability to delegate and to empower teams.
Advocate security and secure practices Advocate security and secure practices
Ability to be a strongly credible ambassador for the FIF brand, including making presentations, and able to establish respect and credibility with media outlets.
Strong skills in analysis, problem solving and negotiation
Ability to work in multicultural Organization
Language Skills
Fluency in English required;
Fluency in FINCA Working languages, e.g. Spanish, Russian and/or French is preferred.
